text.text:
Going to La Mar isn’t going to eat a meal, it’s going to EXPERIENCE a meal.

The flavors are excellent and bring forward exciting Peruvian-Asian fusion tastes. The scallops were a particular highlight, served in gorgeous shells and generously lathered in a crema sauce.

The atmosphere is definitely upscale here — while you could probably get away with wearing a t shirt and jeans, you wouldn’t be out of place in a suit or nice dress, making this a great spot for a dinner date meant to impress or a meal before a night at the opera.

The one hitch was that we weren’t seated until about thirty minutes past our reservation. Luckily, they have a bar at front of house and we were able to get cocktails while we waited. All the same, we were a bit surprised (given that we had a reservation), but understand that hiccups happen.

Overall, it was a romantic experience with food we’re still talking about. Highly recommend.

overview.text: Expansive, waterfront Peruvian restaurant serving ceviche and other seafood dishes, plus cocktails.

description.text:
Upscale Peruvian eatery set on Pier 1 1/2 in the Embarcadero neighborhood with bay views.
The large venue features a bar and outdoor seating on the waterfront patio. It's popular for lunch and dinner, and reservations are recommended. People say the staff is attentive.
The menu focuses on seafood. Popular dishes include empanadas, ceviche, and lomo saltado. Guests also like the pisco sours and the desserts.
Visitors praise the location, the atmosphere, and the views.
Customers typically spend $50–100.

editorialSummary.text: Contemporary waterside seafood eatery serving local oysters and clams, plus craft cocktails.

text.text: Hog Island in San Francisco! Its focus on fresh and delicious seafood makes it one of my favorite spots. I especially recommend their unique version of clam chowder. But overall, everything you order is very good. Its location is perfect for when you’re sightseeing, as this restaurant is in the Ferry Building. Its casual atmosphere, simple menu, and friendly service make it perfect for a relaxed experience. Go between 2pm and 4pm to avoid long wait times during lunch!

originalText.text: Hog Island in San Francisco! Its focus on fresh and delicious seafood makes it one of my favorite spots. I especially recommend their unique version of clam chowder. But overall, everything you order is very good. Its location is perfect for when you’re sightseeing, as this restaurant is in the Ferry Building. Its casual atmosphere, simple menu, and friendly service make it perfect for a relaxed experience. Go between 2pm and 4pm to avoid long wait times during lunch!

text.text:
I popped into this restaurant on a weekday and snagged a table right away. While parking in the area can be pricey ($8/hour!), a quick 7-8 minute walk northeast leads to free street parking and gives you a chance to explore the neighborhood.

The food was fantastic! I started with the Hog Island oysters, which were incredibly fresh and bursting with flavor, without a hint of fishiness. Next, I tried the garlic grilled oysters, cooked to perfection - juicy, creamy, and infused with garlicky goodness. The old bay fries were another highlight - crispy on the outside, fluffy on the inside, and seasoned with a hint of sweetness. Even the ketchup impressed me - tangy and refreshing, it complemented the fries perfectly.

The clam chowder wasn't your typical version. Instead of small bits, it showcased plump whole clams in a slightly thinner, yet still creamy broth that avoided being overly milky.

The service was friendly and attentive, ensuring a smooth and enjoyable dining experience. Plus, considering the high quality of the food, the prices were very reasonable. This hidden gem, even amidst the tourist crowds, offers excellent value and deserves a visit!

text.text: This place lives up to the reviews and rave. We ordered the oysters, clam chowder, mussels, burger, 2 glasses wine and 2 glasses of lager. I was satisfied with it. The clam chowder had a lighter soup to it while the mussels had a thicker stronger taste. Both were wiped out with the bread. The oysters were super fresh. Perfect. I would definitely recommend this place and come back again. There will be a line to queue in. But it was worth it as we were then seated at the table facing Bay Bridge and not facing the queue. It was such a good lunch. In total we spent about usd100 each. There were two of us. If you had more people the cost would be lower.

text.text:
Food was flavorful, but service was not that good.

Drinks took FOREVER to come! Had to wait at least 20-30 minutes is to get the drinks and honestly the restaurant was not even that full.
The servers also did not know who had ordered what drink, and we had to point them out after they call out each item.

They also messed up the order a bit. We asked for the special Barcha Hummus, but they got us all Classic Hummus orders instead.

Portion size was also very small for the price of the food. Appetizers came with 4 pieces each, and even entrees (especially salad) was very small.

Shrimp Skewers were lovely. Nice flavor with a good spice to it!

Zaatar flatbread was delicious - soft and warm and perfect hunt if za'atar.

Arugula Salad (with shrimp, dressing on the side) - nice combination of ingredients, but the volume was very small. Shrimp were nice and crispy, but quite oily.

People enjoyed the Beef Dumplings and Chicken & Specked Ham Croquettas.

Falafel wrap and Chicken Shawarma wrap were also a hit. Lots of fries on the side for those, and good size wrap too.

Chicken shawarma plate with rice seemed to have very little quantity of chicken too.
It was not supremely flavorful but just the right amount of flavor from that rice and chicken together.

Hummus was good, but we really wanted that special Barcha Hummus so kinda sad there.

The menu features dishes from Southern France, Spain, Tunisia, and the Middle East. People recommend the lamb, falafel, and barcha spreads, as well as the drinks.
Guests praise the ambiance and attentive staff. Reservations are recommended.
Customers typically spend $50–100.

The asparagus salad with burrata was amazing and the lamb Kosta was delicious. Definitely get the Barcha spreads. We were curious about what was in one dish and the chef came over and explained everything with enthusiasm. He also told us about another dish we didn't order (the dumplings), but was a crowd favorite. Then he brought us over two dumplings to try! The servers heard it was my birthday so they brought over a piece of cake at the end of the night. The restaurant itself is beautiful and the service was excellent. Highly recommend!

text.text: A good choice for some excellent Mediterranean food. They have indoor seating and an Outdoor Patio. The Barcha Spread was nice but you need to pay for extra bread and they don’t have an Olive oil bottle on the table. The Falafel was a masterpiece. The Vegetarian spread is limited but they are open to tweak dishes for you. I could see a number of people enjoying the Kebabs. Loved the Old Fashioned Cocktail and the service was just superb. Kamal knew the menu and could explain the dishes well and helped us select. A little expensive but in line with the premium location. Worth the experience .

text.text:
Yank Sink offers a nice variety of dim sum, both steamed and fried, that's sure to please dim sum enthusiasts. Conveniently located inside the mall, its dining area extends into the mall itself, creating a casual and relaxed atmosphere.

The service at Yank Sink is efficient, with dim sum carts making rounds for patrons to choose from. Additionally, they offer the option to order some items via QR code, adding a modern touch to the dining experience.

One of the best parts about Yank Sink is its reasonable prices. For just $70, two people can enjoy a satisfying meal without breaking the bank.

In summary, Yank Sink is a solid choice for dim sum lovers looking for a tasty and affordable dining experience in a relaxed setting.

text.text:
I'm sorry to tell you about my experience at STK Steakhouse. Despite the disappointing steak, I must say that the overall ambiance and service at STK Steakhouse were top-notch. The restaurant's chic and trendy atmosphere creates a sophisticated dining experience, perfect for a special occasion or a night out.

The staff at STK Steakhouse were attentive and accommodating, ensuring that our needs were met throughout the meal. The menu offered a variety of options beyond just steak, providing something for everyone to enjoy. The side dishes were flavorful and perfectly complemented the main courses, adding to the overall dining experience. Although I must say the sides were extremely overpriced.

On the downside, the fact that they couldn't get your steak cooked correctly is definitely a disappointment. However, the fact that they refunded it shows that they take customer satisfaction seriously and are willing to make things right when things don't go as planned.

Despite the mishap with the steak, I would still recommend giving STK Steakhouse a try for its overall excellent service, ambiance, and diverse menu offerings. Hopefully, my next visit will be a more positive and satisfying experience.

text.text:
My girlfriend and I go to a new restaurant every week in SF, and we decided to stop by STK after seeing an ad on Instagram.

After reading reviews here about the bad service staff, I wanted to also see if there was any merit to it. Short answer is yes, but because it’s been repeatedly stated in the reviews, it’s not really an employee problem, but a management problem.

When we arrived for lunch, the host (shaved or bald head) didn’t even look us in the eye and seemed a little annoyed we asked for outside seating. He didn’t even seat us at the table — handing us the menus at the door and told us to sit wherever.

The server was initially okay, but when our food came, we had no silverware or napkins, so I just got up and went to the other table to get a couple of sets — as there was no one around to ask.

The $9.99 burger and fries is an amazing deal though. The food was probably 4.5. I’d definitely come back for the burger. I’d like to try the $69.99 a person steak meal another time as well.

I tipped more (25%) even though our server only checked on us once, because I know the food was promotional and normally costs more. I can’t say she deserved it though— having been a bartender, my tipping scale goes from 15% (bad) to 25% (good) 😂.

My girlfriend asked for the burger to be well-done with no pink, and it was pink throughout. She told this to the server when we were paying the bill and she didn’t even apologize, just shrugged. 😂🤦🏻‍♂️

Here’s the reason I’m leaving a review. As we walked out — going through the restaurant — we saw the server and four other employees talking, and made eye contact and said thanks and she ignored us and looked away, and I looked at everyone else and they all looked away. 🤦🏻‍♂️

I saw a previous review that said the staff at Denny’s at 3am is better than this one and I can’t disagree. But once again, that’s on the management for their hiring and training practices. I was thinking, how can they read these reviews and not make changes? As the old saying goes, fool me once… shame on you, fool me twice… shame on me. 😉

The service was attentive and friendly, and poured me a digestif at the end of the meal.

text.text: Great experience, very inviting atmosphere and cozey furniture. Staff were very friendly and helpful with explaining the menu. We enjoyed the 2 course lunch. The cicchetti was delicious - definitely get the meatballs! Our mains were good, but very salty. But would definitely recommend 👌

The cicchetti was delicious - definitely get the meatballs! Our mains were good, but very salty. But would definitely recommend 👌

text.text: A work of art! Everything was well thought out here. Love the atmosphere of entering the restaurant. Feels like you're set back in time. Greeted at the door by two lovely ladies. Check out the cute coat closet, adorbs! The seating was very cozy, generous with pillows. Servers were phenomenal, we had Andreas, he was simply amazing. Very attentive and wonderful with the recommendations. We tried a little of everything. Hands down favorite was the charcuterie board and the risotto. Our table was not a fan of the spritzers but they have a full bar so definitely order your favorite drink. Beautiful gender neutral bathrooms. Will visit again for their lunch menu!

text.text: One of the most special and transportive experiences in San Francisco. It feels as if you are in an Italian lounge in Rome. A wonderful addition to the city in a highly unique location.

text.text: Gorgeous interior! High class and quality service. Perfect for celebrating an anniversary or business meeting. A bit pricey but worth the experience. Food and drinks were very good. Crowd skews older so definitely not a place to get cheap happy hour.

text.text: Beautiful bar with the most amazing fun staff.  Wine and food are wonderful Venetian driven delights.  Carlo and his squad have a world class beverage program that plays to all senses. This is a must go to. Best in the city.
